ixed local density, the star-formation rate (SFR) of low mass\ngalaxies is up to $5.9\\sigma$ enhanced due to connectivity. This SFR boost is\neven more significant ($6.3\\sigma$) for galaxies embedded in cosmic filaments,\nwhere the available matter reservoirs are large. A milder impact is found for\nhigh mass galaxies, hinting at different relative efficiencies of matter inflow\nvia small-scale streams in galaxies of different masses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Jan 2023 10:42:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 3 Feb 2023 15:25:29 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 27 Apr 2023 21:13:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-03"}
