{"id":"2209.05616","submitter":"Chun-Kit  Lai","authors":"Li-Xiang An and Chun-Kit Lai","title":"Product-form Hadamard triples and its spectral self-similar measures","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CA math.FA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In a previous work by {\\L}aba and Wang, it was proved that whenever there is\na Hadamard triple $(N,{\\mathcal D},{\\mathcal L})$, then the associated\none-dimensional self-similar measure $\\mu_{N,{\\mathcal D}}$ generated by maps\n$N^{-1}(x+d)$ with $d\\in{\\mathcal D}$, is a spectral measure. In this paper, we\nintroduce product-form digit sets for finitely many Hadamard triples $(N,\n{\\mathcal A}_k, {\\mathcal L}_k)$ by putting each triple into different scales\nof $N$. Our main result is to prove that the associated self-similar measure\n$\\mu_{N,{\\mathcal D}}$ is a spectral measure. This result allows us to show\nthat product-form self-similar tiles are spectral sets as long as the tiles in\nthe group ${\\mathbb Z}_N$ obey the Coven-Meyerowitz $(T1)$, $(T2)$ tiling\ncondition. Moreover, we show that all self-similar tiles with $N = p^{\\alpha}q$\nare spectral sets, answering a question by Fu, He and Lau in 2015. Finally, our\nresults allow us to offer new singular spectral measures not generated by a\nsingle Hadamard triple. Such new examples allow us to classify all spectral\nself-similar measures generated by four equi-contraction maps, which will\nappear in a forthcoming paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2022 21:11:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
