 to mimic the pupil redundancy. We validate this so-called Redundant\nApodized Pupil (RAP) method on a James Webb Space Telescope-like pupil composed\nof 18 hexagonal segments segments to align, and on the VLT architecture in the\ncase of residual low-wind effect.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Sep 2022 10:08:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
