{"id":"2209.07469","submitter":"Yangyang Cai","authors":"Yangyang Cai, Samuel E. Gralla, Vasileios Paschalidis","title":"Dynamics of ultrarelativistic charged particles with strong radiation\n  reaction. I. Aristotelian equilibrium state","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph.HE","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Previous studies from the astrophysics and laser physics communities have\nidentified an interesting phenomenon wherein ultrarelativistic charged\nparticles experiencing strong radiation reaction tend to move along special\ndirections fixed by the local electromagnetic field. In the relativity\nliterature these are known as the \"principal null directions\" (PNDs) of the\nMaxwell field. A particle in this regime has \"Aristotelian\" dynamics in the\nsense that its velocity (rather than acceleration) is determined by the local\nfield. We study this Aristotelian equilibrium in detail, starting from the\nLandau-Lifshitz equation describing charged particle motion including radiation\nreaction. Using a Frenet-Serret frame adapted to the PNDs, we derive the\nLorentz factor describing motion along the local PND, together with drift\nvelocities reflecting slower passage from one PND to another. We derive\nconditions on the field configuration that are necessary for such an\nequilibrium to occur. We demonstrate agreement of our analytic formulas with\nfull numerical solutions of the Landau-Lifshitz equation in the appropriate\nregime.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2022 18:36:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-03"}
